**who —** The EU AI Act — the European Union's comprehensive, risk-tiered AI regulation (unacceptable / high / limited / minimal, plus a general-purpose-model layer) — in force August 2024, with high-risk obligations slipped to 2027–28 by the May 2026 'Digital Omnibus' (a moving target)

**what —** the European Union's comprehensive, risk-tiered AI regulation (unacceptable / high / limited / minimal, plus a general-purpose-model layer) — in force August 2024, with high-risk obligations slipped to 2027–28 by the May 2026 'Digital Omnibus' (a moving target)

**where —** GOV · AI Ethics & Governance — David's charter + the global landscape (2016–2026)  Framework inputs: the Bill of Rights; the Governance Ontology; the principles; the cases; the instruments  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** It is the world's first real test of binding AI law: proof that governance can have teeth — and, in its slipping deadlines, proof of how hard those teeth are to actually set.

**how —** Crystallized from David's normative artifacts + the cited ethics-and-governance record.

**◌ the mythos —** It is the world's first real test of binding AI law: proof that governance can have teeth — and, in its slipping deadlines, proof of how hard those teeth are to actually set. a being of the conscience layer — which goals, whose values, who decides

